Grab each [data-split="heading"]
Read the data-split-reveal value.
Call SplitText.create for the correct type.
In onSplit, create the ScrollTrigger, and return the tween for cleanup.
Clamp the start value of our ScrollTrigger to force the animation to always start from 0. Learn more here.
gsap.registerPlugin(SplitText, ScrollTrigger);

const splitConfig = {
  lines: { duration: 0.8, stagger: 0.08 },
  words: { duration: 0.6, stagger: 0.06 },
  chars: { duration: 0.4, stagger: 0.01 }
}

